text: Xinavane is a town on the Incomati River, in the Manhiça District of Maputo Province, in Mozambique about 80 kilometres north of Maputo. ==Economy== Tongaat Hulett Sugar grows sugarcane and operates a sugar mill at Xinavane. In 2009 the sugar mill completed a major expansion, engineered and managed by PGBI Engineers & Constructors. ==References== Category:Manhiça District Category:Komati River Category:Populated places in Maputo Province
title: Xinavane
